This paper is primarily focused on vehicular ad hoc networks (VANETs) and their communication protocols, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves the calculation of statistics related to network paths, which could be considered a topic in data structures (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of geodesics to infer location information and protect against collusion attacks, which could be considered topics in security and privacy (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
